{
  "stem": "719.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I never heard it in all my life, because my father wouldn't allow to talk like that-- that anthropology-- not about seven days that God created each day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were so many interesting subjects-- and the right of a girl that is equal-- stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then-- [SIGHS] --they-- they were afraid to meet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We'd-- we'd-- these pictures that I kept through my camp, these are the pictures of that group that we had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a-- a leader-- like one girl, which was older, and she knew more.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was, what in Hebrew it's called [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was the head of that group of the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So she was-- she was-- I don't-- oh, I'm sure she doesn't live.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'm sure, because then we split.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We all went our-- our own ways, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so in 1942, they started to talk about-- oh, no, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Before that, they sent all the residents of this town, which is the famous town-- Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was called Oswiecim in Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's still called Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "German called it the Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Oswiecim was only a few kilometers from where I grew up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what they did, in the beginning before they start to build this place, they took all the Jews, and they-- people used to come into knock in the door, and say, whoever can afford, has room to accommodate, to share your little space that you have with the people-- like immigrants from this town-- into Bedzin.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I-- I do remember that a Jewish committee tried to locate, tried to make room for these Jews, which was only temporary, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because then they were all transported.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at that time, I remember I met new people, people that never lived in this town.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
